						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1742, Vikrama, Jyēshṭha ba. 10.</hi> In this year Jyēshṭha was an intercalary month. If the intended month is Adhika-Jyēshṭha the details of the date correspond to 1820 A.D., June 26, Tuesday. For Nija-Jyēshṭha the details correspond to 1820 A.D., July 24, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a stone <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the Āñjanēya temple by Bāla-Veṅkaṭa-reḍḍi, as a dedication to god Veṅkatēśvara.</p>						

						</summary>
